# Shell scripts must stay LF so they run under bash regardless of the
# checkout's core.autocrlf (a CRLF shebang breaks `bash script.sh`).
*.sh text eol=lf

# Glide isn't in GitHub Linguist yet, so .glide files show up unhighlighted on
# github.com. The syntax is Rust-shaped (fn / let mut / struct / impl / trait /
# match / generics / ::), so render them as Rust for now — it reads far better
# than plain text. Side effect: the language bar counts .glide as Rust; append
# `linguist-detectable=false` below to keep the highlighting but drop it from
# the stats.
*.glide linguist-language=Rust
